This is the Science Fiction Radio Show, a commentary on science fiction and fantasy.

00:36.480 --> 00:46.100
And here are your hosts. This is Bill Vernon and Daryl Lane. How many science fiction works

00:46.100 --> 00:51.120
feature spacecraft capable of planet hopping, interstellar travel, or even galaxy galloping?

00:51.600 --> 00:55.520
Yet in our experience we know it takes several days travel to reach even the moon and years to

00:55.520 --> 01:00.280
reach the nearest planets. Travel to the stars is presently unthinkable. In space opera, the writer

01:00.280 --> 01:04.940
usually invokes some kind of faster than light drive which glosses over the basics of the special

01:04.940 --> 01:09.460
theory of relativity. We asked physicist and science fiction writer Robert Forward how it may be

01:09.460 --> 01:14.580
possible to travel faster than light. When you talk about going faster than light, really what you

01:14.580 --> 01:23.220
want to do is get from here to there without traveling all the steps in between. If you can do

01:23.220 --> 01:29.340
that, then you can go faster than light. There are two ways at least that I know to do that. One is to

01:29.340 --> 01:35.340
find a space warp. You jump into the space warp, you go into a hyperspace, and then you come out of

01:35.340 --> 01:42.180
another space warp somewhere else in our universe. And if you can do that in a time shorter than it

01:42.180 --> 01:49.240
takes you to travel over the top line, then you've done that. And the amazing thing about it is the

01:49.240 --> 01:54.640
Einstein General Theory of relativity has space warps in it. Going through a space warp is one way

01:54.640 --> 02:02.140
to get around the speed of light limit. And what's the second way? Then the other way to go faster

02:02.140 --> 02:09.740
and speed up light is to destroy the space between you and where you want to go. Now this space drive

02:09.740 --> 02:19.080
theory was invented by a student of Roger Penrose. He's a scientific expert and relativist that works

02:19.080 --> 02:27.720
with Hawking on gravitation. And he's working on a thing called twister theory. And in the twister

02:27.720 --> 02:37.060
theory, the real universe is not what we see. That's only a reduced image of it. The real universe is

02:37.060 --> 02:43.040
an eight-dimensional universe that's made up of twisters. The twisters not only make up all the

02:43.040 --> 02:50.800
particles in the space and time that we live in, it even makes up the space and the time. It takes a

02:50.800 --> 02:55.980
certain collection of twisters to make up a point in space. It takes another collection of

02:55.980 --> 03:04.460
twisters to make up a point in time. This collection of twisters is a fairly uniform thing, and that's

03:04.460 --> 03:09.560
why we see space as it is according to Penrose. Now we don't know whether the twister theory is

03:09.560 --> 03:18.180
correct, but Roger is hoping that it will turn out to be an accurate method, I mean accurate theory for the

03:18.180 --> 03:23.760
interest. So how does one build a faster than light drive based on the twister theory of Penrose and his

03:23.760 --> 03:33.720
students? If you want the twister space too much, give it a real strong warp, then it's no longer

03:33.720 --> 03:39.960
ordered well enough to make a piece of space or a piece of time. So if you take a piece of

03:39.960 --> 03:47.200
twister space and you warp it badly, the space and the time that it used to make now disappears. It's

03:47.200 --> 03:53.980
no longer there. So their version of a different kind of a faster than light drive is you take a

03:53.980 --> 03:59.860
spacecraft up, you get it out in the wave in the planets and so forth, then you turn on the

03:59.860 --> 04:09.900
twister warping machine in your spacecraft on the side parts Alpha Centauri and you just warp that

04:09.900 --> 04:17.920
space so much that you warp that twister space so much that the space time between here and Alpha

04:17.920 --> 04:24.080
Centauri disappears. And what you'll see if you're sitting in the spacecraft is that all of a sudden

04:24.080 --> 04:28.520
Alpha Centauri just come right towards you and then pretty soon you look out one window, you see the

04:28.520 --> 04:35.840
sun, you look out the other window, you'll see Alpha Centauri. Then the machine inside the spacecraft

04:36.420 --> 04:42.560
unwarps the space but on the other side of the spacecraft and all that space now reappears between

04:42.560 --> 04:46.580
the spacecraft and the sun, you watch the sun recede off another distance while you stay there

04:46.580 --> 04:51.200
with Alpha Centauri. So that's another way to get there. You just get rid of the space between here

04:51.200 --> 05:03.020
and there. This has been the Science Fiction Radio Show, production of the Permian Basin Science

