simple. It simply involves taking a tune from a normal song and changing the words around to have

26:40.100 --> 26:44.960
something to do with science fiction or fantasy. And usually those are funny and they're the kind

26:44.960 --> 26:47.280
that you can get a lot of giggles off and everyone joins in.

26:47.720 --> 26:54.580
But the more serious element is original songs that deal with very serious ideas like the

26:54.580 --> 26:59.780
fact that man's finally reaching for space and the Columbia's here or the fact that

27:00.340 --> 27:04.080
when are we really going to get to be dancing on the moon by the time it actually happens

27:04.080 --> 27:07.100
I'll be too old and things like that.

27:07.460 --> 27:12.500
And Filking is a whole type of folk singing strictly for fans.

27:13.540 --> 27:18.200
And some fans don't like it because they don't like the taking of other people's music

27:18.200 --> 27:20.060
and putting other lyrics to it.

27:20.240 --> 27:24.500
But for most fans it's a wonderful outlet for getting to know other people and just

27:24.500 --> 27:28.980
sit around at night when there's nothing else to do and sing songs and get a very close

27:28.980 --> 27:34.240
type of camaraderie that you only get in some other kind of very close knit group.

27:34.620 --> 27:39.600
Not all conventions have folk singing but the more intimate ones where it really is

27:39.600 --> 27:44.360
a social life type situation do because it's a very big part of the social life.

27:45.140 --> 27:49.160
Patterson's enthusiasm for science fiction and science fiction fandom is obvious and

27:49.160 --> 27:49.500
infectious.

